> Forget the excessively fried, more-batter-than-fillet version of fish and chips.
> We've come up with a riff that features a lighter panko breadcrumb crust that's
> just as crisp and crunchy. The DIY tartar sauce might just steal the spotlight
> away from the fish, though. Featuring a breath of fresh dill and crunchy
> cucumber bits, it totally trumps the kind from a jar.

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust oven racks to middle and top position. Preheat
oven to 450 degrees. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{2} into ½-inch-thick wedges (like
steak fries). Toss on a #baking sheet{} with @Fry Seasoning{2%tsp} and
@vegetable oil{4%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast potatoes in oven on middle rack until browned and crisp, about
~{25%minutes}, tossing halfway through. On another baking sheet, toss
@broccoli florets{16}(cut) with a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp}, and
a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven on top rack until tender and
crisp, about ~{15%minutes}.

Finely chop @dill{¼%bunch} until you have 1 TBSP. Cut @Persian Cucumber{2}
lengthwise into thin spears. Mince a spear or two until you have 3 TBSP minced
cucumber and set aside in a #small bowl{}.

Add @mayonnaise{4%tbsp} and half the dill to bowl with minced cucumber and stir
to combine. Season to taste with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and up to @white wine
vinegar{2%tsp}. Set aside 4 tsp sauce for brushing fish. In a #medium bowl{},
toss together cucumber spears, remaining @white wine vinegar{2%tsp}, and
@sugar{1%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Microwave @butter{2%tbsp} to melt in another small bowl on high heat, about
~{20%seconds}. (TIP: Alternatively, melt butter in a small pan over medium
heat.) Stir in @panko breadcrumbs{1%cup} and remaining dill. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Once broccoli is done, remove from #baking sheet{} and set
aside. Pat @Catfish{2%fillets} dry with a #paper towel{}, then place on same
baking sheet.

Brush 1 tsp of reserved sauce onto top of each catfish fillet. Press panko
mixture into sauce to adhere. Bake in oven until just opaque, about
~{5%minutes}. Heat broiler to high, then transfer sheet to broiler. Broil until
crust is golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. Divide between plates and serve with
broccoli, potatoes, pickles, and sauce to the side.